<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-14T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/845: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-14T17:00:00+00:00">December
                                    14, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 14—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>609. Department’s 447, December 12, 3 p.m. Foreign Office confirmed again
                            today its understanding that the French Government desires to be in a
                            position to ratify if and when negotiations with Germany are concluded.
                            However, both the French and British Governments are desirous of
                            avoiding a lapse.</p>
                        <p>Ciano has informed Drummond it would be difficult for the Italian
                            Government to sign the treaty until it has been ratified by the original
                            signatories.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>